official_title: A bill to amend the Social Security Act to make certain technical and conforming changes.

summary.text: States that the Secretary of Health, Education, and Welfare may, under the Social Security Act, designate a Professional Standards Review Organization to have jurisdiction over a whole State. Provides that the Secretary shall not refuse to designate any qualified organization as the Professional Standards Review Organization solely because of the number of physicians in such State.
